  "baseLanguage": "hi",
  "targetLanguage": "en",
  "estimatedTime": 45,
  "prerequisites": ["en_hi_M2B4_lesson_001"],
  "instructions": "In English, people speak very fast! They almost never say 'I will'. They smash the two words together to make 'I'll'. This is called a contraction. Listen carefully to how the 'L' sound attaches to the person's name, and practice these 15 future phrases.",
  "contentItems": [
    {
      "type": "note",
      "text": "Touch the tip of your tongue to the roof of your mouth just behind your front teeth to make the sharp 'L' sound!"
    }
  ],
